content:
OmniStudio migration moves the OmniStudio components that you use in a Salesforce Industries Cloud from the OmniStudio managed package runtime to the OmniStudio standard runtime. You may need to migrate if you use Salesforce Industries Insurance, Public Sector Solutions, Communications, Media, or Energy clouds.

Migration is an extended project that you execute in phases over time. Start by checking your cloud’s support for the OmniStudio standard runtime, and then plan the phases of your migration depending on support for features you use such as Angular components.

Available in: Lightning Experience
Available in: Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions
REQUIRED VERSIONS
Available in Winter ’23 and later releases for customers on the custom object model.

To start the process of migrating to OmniStudio Standard, you must have the appropriate licenses for your Salesforce Industries cloud. Confirm with your account executive.

1. Upgrade to the Version of OmniStudio for Vlocity Recommended by Your Salesforce Industries Cloud
2. Convert or Rebuild Angular Components
3. Create Sandboxes
4. Enable the OmniStudio License and Assign Permission Set Licenses
5. Use the Migration Tool to Convert Your OmniStudio Components to the Standard Data Model

WARNING Never run the OmniStudio Migration Tool in your production environment. Run it in your migration sandbox and test thoroughly before deploying to your production environment.

6. Enable Metadata API Support
7. Update References to Point to the Salesforce Standard Data Model
8. Switch to the Standard Runtime and Deploy Components to the Standard Runtime
9. Manually Update Remaining OmniStudio Components to Use the Standard Runtime
10. Migrate Calculation Procedures and Calculation Matrices to the Business Rules Engine and Update OmniStudio Document Generation Templates
11. Test with Your Business Users
12. In Your Production Environment, Deploy the Migrated Components and Enable Licenses and Settings

Enable licenses and settings: OmniStudio Metadata, Managed Package Runtime, and Deploy Custom Lightning Web Components in Standard Runtime. You’ve now completed your migration from the custom data model and the OmniStudio managed package runtime to the Salesforce standard data model and the OmniStudio standard runtime.
title: Migrating to OmniStudio Standard
